.TH "sata_pmp_revalidate" 9 "sata_pmp_revalidate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sata_pmp_revalidate \- revalidate SATA PMP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sata_pmp_revalidate
.BI "(struct ata_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int new_class "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PMP device to revalidate
.IP "new_class" 12
new class code

Re-read GSCR block and make sure \fIdev\fP is still attached to the
port and properly configured.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
